Adedayo Akinwale in Abuja The All Progressives Congress (APC) has commiserated with victims of Sunday morning explosion, which occurred at Abule Ado in Amuwo Odofin Local Government Area of Lagos State, resulting in several injuries, damage to property and deaths. The National Publicity Secretary of the party, Mallam Lanre Issa-Onilu, in a statement issued on Sunday, wished those injured a speedy and full recovery, and also sympathised with residents who lost property in the explosion. The party expressed confidence that the Lagos State government would implement measures to bring succour to the victims. The ruling party also commended the emergency response led by the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA), Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA), the Fire Service and other agencies in quickly containing the incident and attending to injured victims of the explosion.